  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You hold your hand out to the side, performing a simple yet effective throw that violently flips a target creature upside down, knocking the wind out of them.</p><p>Once per round, when you would hit a creature with a melee attack, or a creature would attempt to or successfully Grapple or Restrain you, you can cast this jutsu to force them to make a Dexterity Saving Throw vs. your Martial Arts check. If you have expertise, you add +1d4 instead of doubling your Proficiency Bonus.</p><p>On a success, you knock them Prone and they become Weakened, and their attempt to Grapple or Restrain you fails if they had tried to do so.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank, increase the cost by 3. If this jutsu is cast at B-Rank, you gain a +2 bonus to the Martial Arts check. If this jutsu is cast at S-Rank, you gain a +3 bonus to the Martial Arts check.</p>",
